// an epistemic integrity constraint prunes candidate world views.
// `:- know unsafe().` rejects any world view where `unsafe` is known. Here unsafe()
// is a fact, so the only world view is pruned and the accepted result is empty
// (a semantic pruning, NOT a runtime failure). Expect: accepted with rows: 0.

#pragma epistemic_mode = faeel

pred fact().
pred unsafe().
pred accepted().

fact().
unsafe().

accepted() :- know fact().

:- know unsafe().

?- accepted().
